PROGRAM TO EXPLORE USER-DEFINED (CUSTOM) EXCEPTIONS
      05 March 2026


AIM:
           To demonstrate custom exception in Java.

ALGORITHM:
Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Create a user-defined exception class by extending Exception.
Step 3: Define a constructor in the custom exception class to display an error message.
Step 4: Create the main class.
Step 5: Declare the main() method.
Step 6: Declare required variables (e.g., age, number, etc.).
Step 7: Use a try block.
Step 8: Write a condition to check invalid input (e.g., age < 18).
Step 9: If condition is true, use throw to throw the custom exception.
Step 10: Otherwise, print a valid message.
Step 11: Add a catch block to handle the custom exception.
Step 12: Display the exception message in the catch block.
Step 13: End the program.



